tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.9%), suggesting prediabetes, while fasting glucose is normal. Hematocrit is slightly low, but other red cell indices are within range, indicating possible mild dilutional or early anemia. Platelet distribution width is high, which may reflect increased platelet size variability but platelet count is normal. Renal function, electrolytes, and white cell count are unremarkable. No acute pathology detected; recommend monitoring glycemic status and hematocrit.
